display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> is conjugate to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is conjugate to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex>, which means <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex> is conjugate to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> by <fr:link
type="local"
href="gr-002C.xml"
addr="gr-002C"
title="Conjugation forms an equivalence relation">Conjugation forms an equivalence relation</fr:link>. Hence <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in \mathop {\textrm {Cl}}\nolimits (a)]]></fr:tex>, which establishes <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathop {\textrm {Cl}}\nolimits (b)\subseteq \mathop {\textrm {Cl}}\nolimits (a)]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
